{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "ClOxCycle",
        "description": "Stratospheric ClOx catalytic ozone destruction cycle (Seinfeld & Pandis 2006, Ch. 5 §5.5.1). Migrated from GasChem.jl@8c12c048 src/StratosphericChemistry.jl:272 (`ClOxCycle` @component). Implements 4 ODEs (Cl, ClO, HCl, ClONO2) coupled to 2 algebraic family sums (ClOx = Cl + ClO, Cly = Cl + ClO + HCl + ClONO2). Rate coefficients are Arrhenius (k = A·exp(C/T)) for the five binary reactions and a (T_ref/T)^3.4 form for the termolecular ClO + NO2 + M → ClONO2 channel. All upstream `@constants` are encoded as parameters with their literal SI defaults; physical-condition `@parameters` (T, M, photolysis rates, fixed-bath species O, O3, NO, NO2, OH, CH4) are also parameters so the cycle can be exercised at different atmospheric conditions.",
        "tags": [
            "gaschem",
            "stratospheric",
            "ClOx",
            "ozone-depletion",
            "catalytic-cycle",
            "seinfeld-pandis"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-12T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "GasChem.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (esm-q2id)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Seinfeld, J. H. and Pandis, S. N. (2006). Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics: From Air Pollution to Climate Change, 2nd Edition, John Wiley & Sons. Chapter 5 (Stratospheric Chemistry), §5.5.1 (ClOx catalytic cycle, pp. 162-168), Eqs. 5.29-5.30."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "ClOxCycle": {
            "reference": {
                "notes": "source_ref: GasChem.jl@8c12c048482b515fb8eb2110bf8ab4b4f4e71309:src/StratosphericChemistry.jl:272\n\nUpstream `ClOxCycle` is an MTK `@component` with 12 `@constants` (Arrhenius pre-factors and activation temperatures for five binary channels plus the termolecular ClO + NO2 + M reference), 9 `@parameters` (T, M, j_ClONO2, and the six fixed-bath concentrations CH4, O, O3, NO, NO2, OH), and 6 `@variables` (4 time-indexed states Cl, ClO, HCl, ClONO2 + 2 algebraic family sums ClOx, Cly). All 6 equations preserved verbatim: 4 ODEs (D(Cl), D(ClO), D(HCl), D(ClONO2)) + 2 algebraic (ClOx ~ Cl + ClO, Cly ~ Cl + ClO + HCl + ClONO2). The upstream structural test (test/StratosphericChemistry_test.jl:71-81) asserts `length(equations(sys)) == 6` and that Cl, ClO, ClONO2, ClOx appear as states — both preserved here.\n\nUpstream `@constants` are encoded as parameters with their upstream SI default values, matching the convention used by sibling migrations in this rig (snow_thermal.esm encodes physical constants as parameters with default; diameter_growth.esm encodes R_gas, D_diff similarly). Rate coefficients are written inline in the equations as `A * exp(C / T)` (binary) and `A * (T_ref / T)^3.4` (termolecular ClO + NO2 + M) per Seinfeld & Pandis Table B.1/B.2 (pp. 162-167). CGS→SI conversion factors (cm³/molec/s × 1e-6; cm⁶/molec²/s × 1e-12) are folded into the `_A` defaults: e.g. upstream Cl + O3 pre-factor 2.3e-11 cm³/molec/s → 2.3e-17 m³/s.\n\nCly conservation: the upstream `Cly Conservation (ClOx Cycle)` test (test/StratosphericChemistry_test.jl:266-290) asserts that Cly = Cl + ClO + HCl + ClONO2 is conserved to rtol = 1e-6 over a 1 s integration. This is structurally exact for this component — summing the four ODEs:\n\n    D(Cl)     = -k_Cl_O3·Cl·O3 + k_ClO_O·ClO·O + k_ClO_NO·ClO·NO - k_Cl_CH4·Cl·CH4 + k_OH_HCl·OH·HCl + j_ClONO2·ClONO2\n    D(ClO)    = +k_Cl_O3·Cl·O3 - k_ClO_O·ClO·O - k_ClO_NO·ClO·NO - k_ClO_NO2_M·ClO·NO2·M\n    D(HCl)    = +k_Cl_CH4·Cl·CH4 - k_OH_HCl·OH·HCl\n    D(ClONO2) = +k_ClO_NO2_M·ClO·NO2·M - j_ClONO2·ClONO2\n    Σ         = 0\n\nso D(Cly) ≡ 0 analytically and any observed drift in Cly is integrator roundoff — this is why the upstream test uses rtol = 1e-6 over 1 s while internal solver tolerances run at abstol = 1e-12, reltol = 1e-12. The migration preserves this exact conservation structure.\n\nClOx (= Cl + ClO) is NOT conserved: D(ClOx) = -k_Cl_CH4·Cl·CH4 + k_OH_HCl·OH·HCl + j_ClONO2·ClONO2 - k_ClO_NO2_M·ClO·NO2·M, the four-channel exchange between the active ClOx pair and the reservoir species HCl and ClONO2. The Cl + CH4 / OH + HCl pair shuttles between ClOx and HCl; the ClO + NO2 + M / ClONO2 + hν pair shuttles between ClOx and ClONO2.\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-6): reference trajectories from upstream Julia MTK Tsit5 integration at abstol=1e-10, reltol=1e-10. 1e-6 covers Tsit5↔SciPy LSODA truncation over 3600 s plus float64 roundoff. Cly conservation runs at the same 1e-6 — it matches the upstream test tolerance (test/StratosphericChemistry_test.jl:289). Several anchors test small-fractional deltas near the initial reservoir mass (HCl, ClONO2 changing by 0.1-1% over short windows) — these use looser per-assertion abs floors derived from the variable magnitude (~1e15 m^-3 × 1e-6 = 1e9 abs floor).\n\nDomain validity: this is a stratospheric component. Defaults match the upstream component (T = 227 K and M = 3.1e23 m^-3 are ~30 km conditions; CH4 = 1e19 m^-3, O3 = 3e18 m^-3 are typical stratospheric values). All bath species (O, O3, NO, NO2, OH, CH4) are parameters here because the upstream component treats them as such — this cycle is a sub-model that runs against externally-prescribed environmental conditions, not a self-contained chemistry box. Coupling with the larger StratosphericOzoneSystem (test/StratosphericChemistry_test.jl:94+) is what promotes these to dynamical species; that integration is out of scope for this single-component migration."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1.0e-6
            },
            "variables": {
                "T": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 227.0,
                    "description": "Temperature. Default 227 K matches the upstream component and is the canonical 30 km stratospheric value (Seinfeld & Pandis Table 5.1)."
                },
                "j_ClONO2": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "s^-1",
                    "default": 1.0e-4,
                    "description": "ClONO2 photolysis rate (ClONO2 + hν → Cl + NO3)."
                },
                "CH4": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-3",
                    "default": 1.0e19,
                    "description": "Methane number density (1e13 molec/cm^3 × 1e6 → 1e19 m^-3). Drives the Cl + CH4 → HCl reservoir-formation channel."
                },
                "M": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-3",
                    "default": 3.1e23,
                    "description": "Air number density at 30 km (3.1e17 molec/cm^3 × 1e6 → 3.1e23 m^-3). Third body for the ClO + NO2 + M → ClONO2 termolecular channel."
                },
                "O": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-3",
                    "default": 1.0e13,
                    "description": "Atomic oxygen number density (1e7 molec/cm^3 × 1e6 → 1e13 m^-3). Drives the ClO + O → Cl + O2 catalytic-cycle closing step."
                },
                "O3": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-3",
                    "default": 3.0e18,
                    "description": "Ozone number density (3e12 molec/cm^3 × 1e6 → 3e18 m^-3). Drives the Cl + O3 → ClO + O2 catalytic-cycle initiating step."
                },
                "NO": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-3",
                    "default": 1.0e15,
                    "description": "NO number density (1e9 molec/cm^3 × 1e6 → 1e15 m^-3). Drives the ClO + NO → Cl + NO2 alternative recycling channel."
                },
                "NO2": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-3",
                    "default": 1.0e15,
                    "description": "NO2 number density (1e9 molec/cm^3 × 1e6 → 1e15 m^-3). Reactant in the ClO + NO2 + M → ClONO2 reservoir-formation channel."
                },
                "OH": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-3",
                    "default": 1.0e12,
                    "description": "OH number density (1e6 molec/cm^3 × 1e6 → 1e12 m^-3). Drives the OH + HCl → Cl + H2O reservoir-release channel."
                },
                "k_Cl_O3_A": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^3/s",
                    "default": 2.3e-17,
                    "description": "Arrhenius pre-factor for Cl + O3 → ClO + O2 (upstream constant: 2.3e-11 cm^3/molec/s × 1e-6 → 2.3e-17 m^3/s, Seinfeld & Pandis Table B.1, p. 162)."
                },
                "C_Cl_O3": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": -200.0,
                    "description": "Activation temperature (C = -E_a/R) for Cl + O3 (upstream constant: -200 K, Seinfeld & Pandis p. 162)."
                },
                "k_ClO_O_A": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^3/s",
                    "default": 3.0e-17,
                    "description": "Arrhenius pre-factor for ClO + O → Cl + O2 (upstream constant: 3.0e-11 cm^3/molec/s × 1e-6 → 3.0e-17 m^3/s, Seinfeld & Pandis Table B.1, p. 162)."
                },
                "C_ClO_O": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 70.0,
                    "description": "Activation temperature for ClO + O (upstream constant: 70 K, Seinfeld & Pandis p. 162). Positive C means the reaction speeds up at low T (catalytic cycle is more efficient in the cold stratosphere)."
                },
                "k_ClO_NO_A": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^3/s",
                    "default": 6.4e-18,
                    "description": "Arrhenius pre-factor for ClO + NO → Cl + NO2 (upstream constant: 6.4e-12 cm^3/molec/s × 1e-6 → 6.4e-18 m^3/s, Seinfeld & Pandis Table B.1, p. 163)."
                },
                "C_ClO_NO": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 290.0,
                    "description": "Activation temperature for ClO + NO (upstream constant: 290 K)."
                },
                "k_Cl_CH4_A": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^3/s",
                    "default": 9.6e-18,
                    "description": "Arrhenius pre-factor for Cl + CH4 → HCl + CH3 (upstream constant: 9.6e-12 cm^3/molec/s × 1e-6 → 9.6e-18 m^3/s, Seinfeld & Pandis Table B.1, p. 168)."
                },
                "C_Cl_CH4": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": -1360.0,
                    "description": "Activation temperature for Cl + CH4 (upstream constant: -1360 K — strongly endothermic, slow in the cold stratosphere)."
                },
                "k_OH_HCl_A": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^3/s",
                    "default": 2.6e-18,
                    "description": "Arrhenius pre-factor for OH + HCl → Cl + H2O (upstream constant: 2.6e-12 cm^3/molec/s × 1e-6 → 2.6e-18 m^3/s, Seinfeld & Pandis p. 168)."
                },
                "C_OH_HCl": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": -350.0,
                    "description": "Activation temperature for OH + HCl (upstream constant: -350 K)."
                },
                "k_ClO_NO2_M_A": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^6/s",
                    "default": 1.8e-43,
                    "description": "Pre-factor for the termolecular ClO + NO2 + M → ClONO2 reaction at T_ref = 300 K (upstream constant: 1.8e-31 cm^6/molec^2/s × 1e-12 → 1.8e-43 m^6/s, Seinfeld & Pandis p. 165). Rate is k = A · (T_ref/T)^3.4, not Arrhenius."
                },
                "T_ref_ClO": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 300.0,
                    "description": "Reference temperature for the ClO + NO2 + M rate law k = k_A · (T_ref/T)^3.4."
                },
                "Cl": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m^-3",
                    "default": 1.0e10,
                    "description": "Cl atom number density (upstream default initial value 1e4 molec/cm^3 × 1e6 → 1e10 m^-3)."
                },
                "ClO": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m^-3",
                    "default": 1.0e13,
                    "description": "ClO number density (upstream default initial value 1e7 molec/cm^3 × 1e6 → 1e13 m^-3)."
                },
                "HCl": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m^-3",
                    "default": 1.0e15,
                    "description": "HCl reservoir number density (upstream default initial value 1e9 molec/cm^3 × 1e6 → 1e15 m^-3)."
                },
                "ClONO2": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m^-3",
                    "default": 1.0e15,
                    "description": "ClONO2 reservoir number density (upstream default initial value 1e9 molec/cm^3 × 1e6 → 1e15 m^-3)."
                },
                "ClOx": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m^-3",
                    "description": "Active chlorine family ClOx = Cl + ClO (algebraic). Catalytically destroys O3 via the Cl + O3 / ClO + O cycle."
                },
                "Cly": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "m^-3",
                    "description": "Total inorganic chlorine Cly = Cl + ClO + HCl + ClONO2 (algebraic). Conserved by the four ODEs (D(Cly) ≡ 0)."
                }
            },
            "equations": [
                {
                    "lhs": {"op": "D", "wrt": "t", "args": ["Cl"]},
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "+",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "-",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            -1,
                                            {"op": "*", "args": ["k_Cl_O3_A", {"op": "exp", "args": [{"op": "/", "args": ["C_Cl_O3", "T"]}]}]},
                                            "Cl",
                                            "O3"
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            {"op": "*", "args": ["k_Cl_CH4_A", {"op": "exp", "args": [{"op": "/", "args": ["C_Cl_CH4", "T"]}]}]},
                                            "Cl",
                                            "CH4"
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    {"op": "*", "args": ["k_ClO_O_A", {"op": "exp", "args": [{"op": "/", "args": ["C_ClO_O", "T"]}]}]},
                                    "ClO",
                                    "O"
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    {"op": "*", "args": ["k_ClO_NO_A", {"op": "exp", "args": [{"op": "/", "args": ["C_ClO_NO", "T"]}]}]},
                                    "ClO",
                                    "NO"
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    {"op": "*", "args": ["k_OH_HCl_A", {"op": "exp", "args": [{"op": "/", "args": ["C_OH_HCl", "T"]}]}]},
                                    "OH",
                                    "HCl"
                                ]
                            },
                            {"op": "*", "args": ["j_ClONO2", "ClONO2"]}
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": {"op": "D", "wrt": "t", "args": ["ClO"]},
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "-",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    {"op": "*", "args": ["k_Cl_O3_A", {"op": "exp", "args": [{"op": "/", "args": ["C_Cl_O3", "T"]}]}]},
                                    "Cl",
                                    "O3"
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            {"op": "*", "args": ["k_ClO_O_A", {"op": "exp", "args": [{"op": "/", "args": ["C_ClO_O", "T"]}]}]},
                                            "ClO",
                                            "O"
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            {"op": "*", "args": ["k_ClO_NO_A", {"op": "exp", "args": [{"op": "/", "args": ["C_ClO_NO", "T"]}]}]},
                                            "ClO",
                                            "NO"
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "op": "*",
                                        "args": [
                                            {"op": "*", "args": ["k_ClO_NO2_M_A", {"op": "^", "args": [{"op": "/", "args": ["T_ref_ClO", "T"]}, 3.4]}]},
                                            "ClO",
                                            "NO2",
                                            "M"
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": {"op": "D", "wrt": "t", "args": ["HCl"]},
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "-",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    {"op": "*", "args": ["k_Cl_CH4_A", {"op": "exp", "args": [{"op": "/", "args": ["C_Cl_CH4", "T"]}]}]},
                                    "Cl",
                                    "CH4"
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    {"op": "*", "args": ["k_OH_HCl_A", {"op": "exp", "args": [{"op": "/", "args": ["C_OH_HCl", "T"]}]}]},
                                    "OH",
                                    "HCl"
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "lhs": {"op": "D", "wrt": "t", "args": ["ClONO2"]},
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "-",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    {"op": "*", "args": ["k_ClO_NO2_M_A", {"op": "^", "args": [{"op": "/", "args": ["T_ref_ClO", "T"]}, 3.4]}]},
                                    "ClO",
                                    "NO2",
                                    "M"
                                ]
                            },
                            {"op": "*", "args": ["j_ClONO2", "ClONO2"]}
                        ]
